Jeanette Chabalala, News24(News24, file) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban &ndash; Three family members sustained serious injuries after a parcel they opened exploded on Friday, KwaZulu-Natal police said.The family were in their house in Essenwood, Durban when they received the parcel, Captain Nqobile Gwala &nbsp;said.She said the three people were taken to a hospital. The explosives unit and Berea SAPS are still at the scene. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.